        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1872-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1872-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="149" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <head>No. 14.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Schenck</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-04-01">1<hi rend="italic">st April</hi>,
                                1872</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Have you any objection to British Government filing Counter Case, without
                            prejudice to their position in regard to consequential damages?</p>
                <p>Received at 9.40 a.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>SCHENCK.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
